<P>
   The following Arizona Republic story has been added for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Thursday, July 16. If you
have any questions, please contact the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
AMWEST _ From the moment America West Airlines fired 500 mechanics
three years ago, some workers in the airline's hangar have sounded
dire warnings about lax maintenance. In the minds of the mechanics,
the Federal Aviation Administration validated their worries Tuesday
by levying a $5 million fine against the Tempe airline for
maintenance lapses. By DAWN GILBERTSON. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL;
</P>
