<HEADLINE>
BRITISH OPEN NOTEBOOK: DALY BATTLES, LOVE'S BACK 
</HEADLINE>
  (nk) 
 By CLIFTON BROWN   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   SOUTHPORT, England _ John Daly was his usual forthcoming self
Wednesday, revealing that he had reunited with his wife, Paulette,
who had filed for divorce last year.``I'm back with my wife, which
was really a miracle in itself,'' said Daly, who won the 1995
British Open. ``We got back together about two months ago. So
things actually in my life are really good now.''
</P>
<P>
   Daly also talked about the daily challenge he faces as a
recovering alcoholic. He laughed when asked if he was having
trouble finding meetings for recovering alcoholics in England.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's drunks all over this world, man, we're everywhere,''
he said. ``I've been doing real well for the last year and three
months. My body has changed an awful lot. Physically, I'm
overweight and out of shape. You go from one addiction to another,
and mine seems to be food. Hopefully that will change in a few
years of sobriety.
</P>
<P>
   ``I still have cravings for the sugar. For people who don't
know, if you're an alcoholic like I am, you crave sugar when you
quit drinking because alcohol turns to sugar in your body. Europe
has the greatest chocolate in the world. I don't know which is
going to be my pick on the golf course. I have not found it yet,
but I'm sure I will. It's too cold to eat ice cream.''
</P>
<P>
   Love's Back Problems
</P>
<P>
   Davis Love III said his back, which bothered him for several
months, was feeling as good as it has in many months. He has been
given clearance to do whatever he wants to on the golf course, and
he does not expect to have recurring problems throughout his
career, as long as he stays in shape.
</P>
<P>
   ``I hurt my back, but I don't have a bad back,'' said Love, who
won last year's PGA Championship. ``Fred Couples has a bad back. No
matter what he does, he's going to have problems. Me, as long as I
don't do anything crazy, don't play five or six straight weeks, and
take care of myself, I should be OK.
</P>
<P>
   ``But the flight over here was funny, because I'm not supposed
to sit in one place for too long, and every time I got up, it
seemed like they turned the seat belt sign on. After a while, I was
hiding in the back from the flight attendants, so they wouldn't see
me.''
</P>
</TEXT>
