   &UR; BUSINESS DAY _ (Moved in ``f'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BANKS-LENDING (Undated) _ Bankers and federal regulators are
growing more concerned about the free-wheeling lending practices of
some banks. By Timothy L. O'Brien.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT grpahics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   BRAZIL-SCHOOLS (Pacajus, Brazil) _ As foreign companies buy up
state-owned industries in Brazil, putting their money in everything
from car factories to pharmaceutical manufacturers, they are
finding that productivity and quality control are being hampered by
the nation's poor educational system. By Diana Jean Schemo.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   PUERTO-ECONSCENE _ To most Americans, the idea of a
government-owned telephone system is no doubt as alien, say, as
driving on the left side of the road. But to Puerto Ricans the
proposed privatization of the state-run telephone company is a
fighting issue, with a majority apparently preferring Big Brother
to big business. By Peter Passell.
</P>
<P>
   COCA-COLA-MARKETPLACE _ Coca-Cola Enterprises Inc., the bottling
company that is ever the bridesmaid to the giant Coca-Cola Co., is
getting a turn in the spotlight after all. By Constance L. Hays.
</P>
<P>
   FORD-AD-COLUMN _ Ford Motor Co. has unexpectedly shaken up its
agency roster across Europe, shifting assignments with billings
estimated at $175 million to $225 million to Young &AMP; Rubicam
Advertising from Ogilvy &AMP; Mather Worldwide. By Stuart Elliott.
</P>
<P>
   BRAZIL-SCHOOLS (Pacajus, Brazil) _ As foreign companies buy up
state-owned industries in Brazil, putting their money in everything
from car factories to pharmaceutical manufacturers, they are
finding that productivity and quality control are being hampered by
the nation's poor educational system. By Diana Jean Schemo.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CULTURE (Moved in ``e'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   DOWNLOADING-MUSIC (Undated) _ The sound that could transform the
music business is the quiet click of a computer mouse. It is
possible to download, free or for a price, high-fidelity songs and
full-length albums that can join a permanent collection. For those
who have been sending and receiving music via the Internet, digital
distribution is a harbinger of a future when recorded music has
been freed entirely from physical form. Sold or disseminated as
bytes rather than disks, it joins the worldwide flow of digital
information. By Jon Pareles.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo [NYT11) has been sent to NYT photo clients.)
</P>
<P>
   BARCELONA-OPERA (Barcelona, Spain) _ A rebuilt opera house is
set to open in Barcelona. By Alan Riding.
</P>
<P>
   ATATURK-FILM (Undated) _ Debate over the political legacy of
Mustafa Kemal Atat5rk, the founder of modern Turkey, has upset
plans for a film about him that was to have starred Antonio
Banderas. By Stephen Kinzer.
</P>
