<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKC-ASU-UNLV-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SUN DEVILS TO FACE UNLV IN BASKETBALL 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB COHN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - The Arizona State men's basketball team will battle
Nevada-Las Vegas for just the second time ever as part of a
doubleheader at America West Arena on Dec. 5.
</P>
<P>
   Arizona plays Wyoming in the other game. Times have not been
set, but ASU-UNLV likely will be the first game and start early in
the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   The teams met once before, during the NCAA Tournament in 1975.
ASU won, 84-81.
</P>
<P>
   ``With the proximity of the two schools, it's amazing when you
look in the record book and see they've played only once in
history,'' said ASU Sports Information Director Mark Brand, who
works on the scheduling. ``Maybe we can start something here.''
</P>
<P>
   UNLV basketball declined in the wake of former head coach Jerry
Tarkanian's conflicts with the NCAA, his subsequent departure and
Rollie Massimino's brief but unhappy tenure. But the program has
enjoyed a resurgence under the current head coach, Bill Bayno.
</P>
<P>
   The Runnin' Rebels went 20-13 last season and earned an
automatic NCAA Tournament berth by winning the Western Athletic
Conference tournament.
</P>
<P>
   ASU went 18-14 last season under former Coach Don Newman. Rob
Evans will coach the team this season.
</P>
<P>
   The rest of the Sun Devils' schedule is expected to be announced
in a few days. &QL;
</P>
