<P>
   LATHAM-COLUMN _ I was standing in the line at the grocery store
and, boy, was I hot. It had nothing to do with the near-triple
digit temperatures outside. No, I was hot as in angry. Angry at the
world, at the store management, at the cashier, and most especially
of all at the woman who had dumped half a million products on the
check-out line in front of me. (Latham, Marshall News Messenger)
MOVED.
</P>
