   REAL-LIFE _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ He gets up before 6 because
when you're 84, that's just what you do. George Chalhub started
growing things 52 years ago on this patch of land not far from what
today is Palm Beach International Airport. There's development all
around his little town of Glen Ridge now. That leaves George
Chalhub, a man who leads a quiet life in a busy place. (Minor, Palm
Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
