David Harris writes: ``I take excellent care of our three cars
(change the oil every 2,500 miles, etc.), but I buy the cheapest
gasoline I can find. How do I determine which fuel is a
good-quality fuel?'' (Carter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TESTDRIVE _ ATLANTA _ Chevrolet likes to bill its Malibu sedan,
a midsize model larger than the Cavalier and smaller than the
Lumina, as ``the car you knew America could build.'' The question
that phrase begs, naturally, is, ``Well, why did it take so long?''
(DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
