</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE WEDNESDAY SPECIAL ADVISORY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These feature stories for release Friday, July 17, 1998, are
moving today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   Separate budgets move daily with spot news, sports, business and
commentary.
</P>
<P>
   Stories are moving in the category they're listed under. Stories
moving to duplicate categories are marked. All stories have moved
except those with an ETA.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   SWINGDANCING PACKAGE FROM THE AUSTIN AMERICAN-STATESMAN
</P>
<P>
   MOVING IN THE E-ENTERTAINMENT CATEGORY
</P>
<P>
   SWING-INTRO _ Swing is in the air, and this is one retro
movement that has captured the full attention of the modern
marketing machine. (Corcoran, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SWING-PRIMER _ Swing is what happened when the best jazz
musicians in the world were hired to play dance music for the
masses. Like gold medal skaters doing a figure 8, the idea was to
find a way to flourish within the routine. Sophistication ruled the
bandstand, leading to an overall quality of performance that makes
choosing the best recorded music from the era such a hard task. But
if you're new to the scene and want to do some catching up, you
could do a lot worse than this starter kit: (list of music
follows). (Corcoran, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SWING-GUY _ I'm strictly freestyle, you know? I go to a club,
step up to the floor and get my groove on. I'm a free spirit, a
nonconformist to prescribed steps. In other words I ... don't know
how to dance. But recently, the indie hit ``Swingers'' made swing
dance lessons safe for young men like myself. On a Monday night, I
went over to the Caucus Club (Austin, Texas), where upwards of 50
students are packed elbow to elbow on the dance floor. (Hibberd,
Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BANDS-&AMP;-STYLES _ We called them lounge bands just a year and a
half ago, but no matter. If you want to get into the swing of
things, these are the groups to go out and see for that full
hipster experience. These are the groups making waves across the
country with swing music, helping it wash up everywhere from the
Billboard charts to MTV. Besides three- and four-word names, they
all have hectic tour schedules in common. (Riemenschneider, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
