<P>
   CZAR-YELTSIN _ ST. PETERSBURG, Russia _ President Boris Yeltsin
silenced all the rumors Thursday when he announced that he would
attend the royal burial ceremony for the bones of Nicholas II,
Russia's last czar, and his family. Yeltsin, like many other
high-level dignitaries, had earlier said that he would not attend
the Friday ceremony largely because the powerful Russian Orthodox
Church cast doubt on whether the bones were authentic. (Holmes, Cox
News Service).
</P>
