</P>
<P>
   WHITEWATER-PROFILE _ A profile of the company that owns White
Water park, linked to E. coli infections of at least two dozen
children. Silver Dollar City is one of the most respected names in
the amusement industry. One of the owners of the Branson, Mo.
company says he was so upset when he heard news of the outbreak
that he cried, but stops short of promising to pay medical bills
incurred by parents of the victims. Silver Dollar City, operated by
the Herschend family, has grown one of the nation's largest
amusement companies from a hole in the ground. From its beginning
of setting up some craft stands at the mouth of a Missouri cave and
charging admission, the company grown into an operator of river
boats, water parks in several cities and even Dollywood.
(Schneider, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
