<P>
   BOOK-SPOCK-HNS (Undated) _ ``Dr. Spock: An American Life'' is
more than a well-researched biography of America's favorite baby
doctor; it is fascinating social history that reads like a great
adventure. By Carolyn Poirot.
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-AUTHOR-AZR (Undated) _ Roy Blount Jr. says much of ``Be
Sweet'' is about his difficult relationship with his mother and how
his self-loathing is at the heart of his comedy efforts. By Anne
Stephenson.
</P>
<P>
   NANCY-DREW-NYT (Undated) _ The figure of the eternally competent
Nancy Drew has been a magnet for scholars who read into the Nancy
Drew books the trajectory of American womanhood throughout the
course of the century.
</P>
<P>
   MCINERNEY-FASHION-NOVEL-NYT (New York) _ From the moment that
Jay McInerney's hapless hero of his upcoming novel shaloms through
a crowd of air kissing New York fashionistas at the ``Party You
Have Been to 600 Times Already,'' you are utterly prepared for some
176 pages of haute-runway literature. You would, however, be
mistaken, insisted McInerney, who said that fashion is simply one
strand of his new novel, ``Model Behavior,'' which chronicles the
unraveling relationship of a fashion magazine journalist and his
size 6 girlfriend who is gainfully employed as a model in the New
York hothouse of fashion, where appearance is destiny and
``breathless enthusiasm sings harmony with toxic ennui.'' By Doreen
Carvajal.
</P>
