raising hopes that for the first time a vaccine can be devised
against it. The pathogen is Treponema pallidum, the organism that
causes syphilis. Its full DNA or genome, containing the entire
instruction set needed to infect and thrive in human cells, has now
been deciphered by biologists at the Institute for Genomic Research
in Rockville, Md., and the University of Texas Health Science
Center in Houston. By Nicholas Wade.
