He tells us why he can still outperform despite the fact that Blue
Chips look pricey. By William R. Long.
</P>
<P>
   MUTFUND-DICARLO-NYT (Undated) _ Profile of Michael DiCarlo, well
known manager of the once top performing John Hancock Special
Equities fund, who lost his bearings. By Carole Gould.
</P>
<P>
   FUNDS-WATCH-NYT (Undated) _ New study explains what kinds of
funds suffer most from asset growth. By Carole Gould.
</P>
<P>
   MUTUAL-FUNDS-BLOOM (Stamford, Conn.) _ Cendant Corp.'s debacle
is bruising some of the nation's biggest fund managers, including
Morgan Stanley Dean Witter &AMP; Co., Alliance Capital Management and
MFS Investment Management. They've all made big bets on the
fortunes of the direct marketer and franchiser, which owns brands
including Avis Rent-A-Car and Howard Johnson's hotels. By Katherine
Burton.
</P>
<P>
   TAKING-STOCK-BLOOM (New York) _ U.S. food company stocks are
getting snubbed by the economy's boom, as consumers have gotten
stingy in the supermarket. The companies haven't helped themselves
by cutting ad budgets and raising prices over the past few years,
giving a boost to supermarket brands that stress low prices. Now,
food companies have to play catch up. By Noam Neusner
</P>
<P>
   MUTUAL-FUNDS-BLOOM (New York) _ Holders of mutual funds that
invest in mortgage-backed securities should view their recent
tumble as a temporary setback, not a sell signal, analysts said. By
Dave Liedtka.
</P>
<P>
   FIDELITY-FUNDS-HOLDINGS-BLOOM (Boston) _ Fidelity Investments'
three largest funds, including its flagship Magellan Fund, are
concentrating their holdings in fewer stocks, according to a report
from the company. By Richard Chimberg.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY &LR;
</P>
