readers have fuel-related questions, two about fuel quality and one
about gas stations. Let's tackle the confusion about fuel first.
David Harris writes: ``I take excellent care of our three cars
(change the oil every 2,500 miles, etc.), but I buy the cheapest
gasoline I can find. How do I determine which fuel is a
good-quality fuel?'' (Carter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
