   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CZAR-SQUABBLE (St. Peterburg, Russia) -- When Boris Yeltsin
proposed reburying Czar Nicholas and family, he hoped Russia would
symbolically bury the sins of the past. Instead, the ceremony, to
be held Friday, has disintegrated into petty political squabbling.
By David Filipov. 1200 words.,
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CALIF-PRIMARY (Washington) -- California appears to be on verge
