<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AEROSMITH-DRUMMER-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AEROSMITH DRUMMER RECOVERING FROM BURNS 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (a and e coding)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By STEPHEN KIEHL  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The investigation into the cause of a car fire that injured
Aerosmith drummer Joey Kramer Wednesday night focused Thursday on a
pool of gasoline that witnesses saw beneath the car before the
fire.
</P>
<P>
   Kramer, 46, suffered second-degree burns on his left arm and
minor burns on his legs. He was pulled from his burning 1998
Ferrari by an attendant at a gasoline station in Scituate, Mass.
Kramer was sitting in the driver's seat when the flames engulfed
the car.
</P>
<P>
   Kramer, who was released after treatment at hospital, could not
be reached for comment Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The fire, which produced flames that reached 15 feet, destroyed
the car and damaged a gasoline pump.
</P>
<P>
   The gasoline may have leaked from a ruptured fuel line or a
faulty gasoline pump, said fire officials. The tip of the nozzle of
the gasoline hose snapped off inside the fuel tank of Kramer's
Ferrari.
</P>
<P>
   The owner of the station, Gerald Gorman, said the pump was in
good condition and that it had serviced ``thousands'' of cars
without incident.
</P>
<P>
   The fumes from the pool of gasoline may have been ignited by the
intense, 1,500-degree heat generated by the car's catalytic
converters, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators said the car was running while the gasoline tank
was being filled, which is illegal and increases the chance of
fire. The engine in the Ferrari is in the middle of the car, near
the gasoline tank.
</P>
<P>
   ``If the fuel line had lost its integrity and the product
leaking out of the fuel line puddled underneath the car and came in
contact with hot engine parts, there is the potential of fire,''
said Scituate Deputy Fire Chief Charles Curran.
</P>
<P>
   Making sure that a motorist shuts off his car engine while
fueling is the reponsibility of a gasoline station owner. Gorman
said he did not know whether the Ferrari's engine was running.
</P>
<P>
   An Aerosmith spokeswoman in New York said Kramer is resting at
his home in Marshfield Hills, Mass. with his wife, April. An
Aerosmith tour scheduled for later this summer will go forward as
scheduled.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
