<HEADLINE>
JOHN BIRCH SOCIETY IS NAMED AFTER MISSIONARY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: How did the John Birch Society get its name? _ J.S., Stuart,
Fla.
</P>
<P>
   A: When a group led by Robert Welch founded the society in 1958,
they took the name of Capt. John Birch, a Christian missionary
killed in China 10 days after the end of World War II.
</P>
<P>
   Birch went to China in 1940 to fight communism, and he assisted
U.S. military efforts against Japan during the war. He died at age
26 after being shot by Chinese communists, according to the John
Birch Society World Wide Web site at www.jbs.org.
</P>
<P>
   ``If we rediscover some of our sounder spiritual values in the
example of his life ... and learn essential truths about our enemy
from the lesson of his murder, then his death at 26 ceases to be a
tragedy,'' Welch states on the site.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Bill Pullman? _ T.S., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Pullman in care of United Talent Agency, 9560
Wilshire Blvd., Suite 500, Beverly Hills, CA 90212.
</P>
<P>
   The 45-year-old actor recently finished work on his 34th film,
``Brokedown Palace,'' with Claire Danes and Lou Diamond Phillips.
The movie is about two vacationing women who are arrested for
smuggling in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
   This month, Pullman began work in Vancouver, British Columbia,
on the film ``Lake Placid,'' publicist Karen Goldstein said.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
