<HEADLINE>
ZAMORA'S ATTORNEY MAY SEEK NEW TRIAL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JAN JARVIS 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Testimony from a new witness given during
David Graham's trial Wednesday has prompted an attorney for Diane
Zamora to consider seeking a new trial for his client, who in
February was convicted of capital murder in the death of
16-year-old Adrianne Jones.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a possibility, but we haven't crossed that bridge yet,''
said Zamora's defense attorney, John Linebarger of Fort Worth.
</P>
<P>
   The new evidence on which Linebarger said he might base an
appeal was presented Wednesday when Wendy Bartlett, a former
cross-country teammate of Jones and Graham. Bartlett testified that
she drove Jones home from a track meet the night that Graham said
in his police confession that the two had a tryst.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutor Mike Parish said Wednesday that investigators were
unaware of the new witness until a month ago.
</P>
<P>
   Linebarger said that he had heard rumors that there was new
evidence by a witness who would testify in Graham's trial. ``Quite
frankly, I was shocked when I heard that,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Linebarger said prosecutors have never given him Bartlett's name
as a witness.
</P>
<P>
   Zamora, Graham's former fiancee, was convicted in the fatal
beating and shooting of Jones, a Mansfield High School sophomore.
Graham is on trial in New Braunfels, Texas, in that killing.
</P>
<P>
   Linebarger said he will probably ask for a hearing to supplement
the record on the appeal that has been filed in Zamora's case. To
do that, Linebarger said, he will have to file an out-of-time
motion for a new trial based on newly discovered evidence.
</P>
<P>
   Normally, attorneys have 30 days after their client is found
guilty to file. But Linebarger said that based on the new evidence,
he believes he can file for a new trial.
</P>
<P>
   He said he will wait until after the Graham trial to file for a
new trial because he wants to get a transcript of the testimony.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
