<P>
   &UR; BILL'S WORLD &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By Bill Tammeus, The Kansas City Star &LR;
</P>
<P>
   If its agents have to testify about the president's love life,
the name may have to be changed to the Seek-it Service.
</P>
<P>
   Ken Starr wants the Secret Service to tell him where Bill
Clinton has spent his evenings. Our guess: Hiding out to avoid Al
Gore's speeches.
</P>
<P>
   Marv Albert is returning to broadcasting. Did one of the
networks need someone experienced to do play-by-play of the Clinton
investigation?
</P>
<P>
   The Year 2000 computer problem, says Mr. Clinton, is not
susceptible to a single government program or an easy fix.'' Odd.
That's not what politicians tell us about the rest of life.
</P>
<P>
   Mr. Clinton says a stable'' Russia is critical to our long-term
national interests.'' Sounds like he wants to limit Vodka
consumption.
</P>
<P>
   Bobby Rush, once a Black Panther and now a member of Congress,
is running for mayor of Chicago. Some folks prefer not to wait but
to get their disappointments Daley.
</P>
<P>
   Average worldwide temperatures have set record highs each month
this year, it's reported. Global warming proponents may not be
right, but it's harder now to make the case for global cooling.
</P>
<P>
   The stock market has been in record high territory lately. In
fact, the
</P>
<P>
   Dow is roughly equivalent to Mark McGwire hitting 94 homers this
season.
</P>
<P>
   A jacket-airbag for motorcycle riders will go on sale soon in
Japan. The man at the next desk says he's been in staff meetings in
which he could have used one of those.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Overheard at a country funeral &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't just lose a brother here today ... I lost a cousin,
father, and husband as well.'
</P>
<P>
   &UR; One Liners &LR;
</P>
<P>
   A.A.A.A.A. - An organization for drunks who drive.
</P>
<P>
   For a REAL sponge cake, BORROW all the ingredients.
</P>
<P>
   Paper clips are the larval stage of coat hangers.
</P>
<P>
