<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, JULY 17
</HEADLINE>
  Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-IRAN-RUSSIA-U.S.-NYT (moved on Wednesday, July 15)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, July
15, about American sanctions against nine Russian enterprises
included an outdated description of one company, Glavkosmos. It is
private and acts as a broker of space and missile technology; it is
no longer a Government space agency.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-BREAST-IMPLANTS-NYT (moved on Tuesday, July 14)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, July 14,
about a British report on the safety of silicone breast implants
referred incorrectly to Dr. Robert Garry of Tulane University. He
has given a deposition in support of plaintiffs in a class-action
suit involving the implants, and has appeared at a news conference
arranged on behalf of lawyers representing women who are suing
implant makers. But he has not testified frequently on behalf of
plaintiffs in implant trials.
</P>
</TEXT>
