   (NYT22) NEW YORK -- July 16, 1998 -- HBO-BOXING-PROMOMAN, 7-16
-- Programming chief for HBO boxing, Lou DiBella, in Bryant Park,
promoting the upcoming Saturday night fight on HBO featuring
light-heavyweight champion Roy Jones Jr. (in background), at
Madison Square Garden. A Harvard Law graduate, raised in Flatbush,
Brooklyn, DiBella has the power to help determine what boxing
matches HBO's audience will see. ``My Ivy League education gave me
the education to deal with the Don Kings or Bob Arums of the
world,'' says DiBella. (Librado Romero/New York Times Photo)
