BURLESQUE-MEMORIES, 7-16 -- Dixie Evans in the ``Jenny Lee'' room
of her Exotic World museum, dedicated to the history of burlesque
and stripper stars from the 20s to the 50s. ``These people deserve
their place in entertainment history,'' says Miss Evans, who was
once billed as the Marilyn Monroe of Burlesque. The museum is in a
one-story building that used to be a series of goat sheds on what
used to be a 40-acre goat farm. ``There's only one old goat left,''
says Miss Evans, ``and that's me.'' (Edward Carreon/New York Times
Photo)
