President Clinton greeting Rep. William J. Jefferson of New Orleans
Thursday after speaking out for patients' rights on Capitol Hill.
Clinton declared to a crowd of doctors and Democratic colleagues
that a patient's right to sue should be a cornerstone of managed
care legislation. Republicans squabbled among themselves, with some
disagreeing over the extent of legal protections that should be
afforded to patients and whether the proposals would fuel rising
health costs. (Paul Hosefros/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) DECANI, Serbia -- July 16, 1998 -- YUGO-ALBANIANS, 7-16
-- Shukrie Shala, far right, the mother of five, has not heard from
her husband, Dr. Hafir Shala, an ethnic Albanian who worked in a
clinic run by Mother Teresa's Sisters of Charity mission in
Glogovac, since he was seized by the Serbian police on April 10.
Serbian forces have been turning increasingly to the abduction and
execution of small groups of civilians in their fight against
ethnic Albanian separatists in Kosovo, according to human rights
officials and witnesses. (Wade Goddard/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
