<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- July 16, 1998 -- MARATHON-SWIMMER, 7-16 --
Marathon swimmer Shelley Taylor-Smith during an interview. Last
Saturday, at 36, she won the 28.5-mile Manhattan Island Marathon
for the fifth time, seizing the lead from two men in their 20s who
were half a mile ahead. ``All of a sudden I'm coming down
Manhattan, and I'm winning,'' says Ms. Taylor-Smith who has decided
to retire. ``Never in my wildest dreams did I think I would end my
career on such a fairy tale note.'' (Librado Romero/New York Times
Photo)
