<P>
   &QL; 
ABORT (Phoenix) _ The A-Z Women's Health Center, where two women
bled to death in the past three years and a full-term baby was
almost aborted last month, operated free of scrutiny by Arizona
health-care officials. In fact, of the 14 Valley clinics that
advertise abortion services, only six are licensed by the Arizona
Department of Health Services, according to state records. By JODIE
SNYDER and HEATHER RATCLIFFE. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
